=Gao seng zhuan 高僧傳 Biographies of eminent monks=
* 高僧傳, later called 梁高僧传, hagiographical work by [[慧皎]] (497-554), [[@http://www.cbeta.org/result/T50/T50n2059.htm|Taisho Vol.50 Nr.2059]] 
* 續高僧傳, later called 唐高僧傳, hagiographical work by [[道宣]](596～667)
* 宋高僧傳 or 大宋高僧傳, hagiographical work by [[贊寧]] （919－1001）
* 大高僧傳 or 大明高僧傳, hagiographical work

==Literature==
===Translations===
* [[Robert Shih]]: Biographies des Moines Éminents (Kao seng tchouan) de Houei-kiao: Biographies des premiers Traducteurs. Volume 1, Louvain: Institute Orientaliste, 1968 

===Monographs===
* John Kieschnick: The eminent monk: Buddhist ideals in medieval Chinese hagiography. Honolulu: Univ. of Hawaii Press, 1997.

===Dissertations===
* John Kieschnick: The Idea of the Monk in Medieval China : Asceticism, Thaumaturgy, and Scholarship in the 'biographies of Eminent Monks'. PhD, Stanford University, 1995. [[http://proquest.umi.com/pqdweb?did=741753621&sid=1&Fmt=6&clientId=21097&RQT=309&VName=PQD%20|ProQuest]] 
* Robin Beth: Buddhism, biography and power: A study of Daoxuan's "Continued Lives of Eminent Monks", PhD, Harvard University, 1995. [[@http://proquest.umi.com/pqdweb?did=740909191&sid=2&Fmt=6&clientId=21097&RQT=309&VName=PQD%20|ProQuest]] 

